arn.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the Queue.

description.description: Specifies the description of the Queue.

hoursOfOperationId.description: Specifies the identifier of the Hours of Operation.

instanceId.description: Specifies the identifier of the hosting Amazon Connect Instance.

maxContacts.description: Specifies the maximum number of contacts that can be in the queue before it is considered full. Minimum value of 0.

name.description: Specifies the name of the Queue.

outboundCallerConfig.description: A block that defines the outbound caller ID name, number, and outbound whisper flow. The Outbound Caller Config block is documented below.

quickConnectIds.description: Specifies a list of quick connects ids that determine the quick connects available to agents who are working the queue.

status.description: Specifies the description of the Queue. Valid values are `ENABLED`, `DISABLED`.

tags.description: Tags to apply to the Queue. If configured with a provider `default_tags` configuration block present, tags with matching keys will overwrite those defined at the provider-level.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
